{"id":"285303776_DIFFERENTIAL_ITEM_FUNCTIONING_AND_THE_MANTEL-HAENSZEL_PROCEDURE","abstract":"The Mantel-Haenszel procedure is a noniterative contingency table method for estimating and testing a common two-factor association parameter in a 2×2×k table. As such it may be used to study “item bias” or differential item functioning in two groups of examinees. This technique is discussed in this context and compared to other related techniques as well as to item response theory methods.","authors":["Paul W. Holland","Dorothy T. Thayer"],"meta":["December 1986ETS Research Report Series 1986(2):i-24","DOI:10.1002/j.2330-8516.1986.tb00186.x"],"references":["250185575_Accounting_for_Statistical_Artifacts_in_Item_Bias_Research","40933482_Discrete_Multivariate_Analysis_Theory_and_Practice","38360107_Conditional_Association_and_Unidimensionality_in_Monotone_Latent_Variable_Models","313702965_Statistical_aspects_of_the_analysis_of_data_from_retrospective_studies_of_disease","301957188_Statistical_Aspects_of_the_Analysis_of_Data_From_Retrospective_Studies_of_Disease","285303880_An_alternative_definition_of_the_ETS_delta_scale_of_item_difficulty","285276385_Characterizing_the_manifest_probabilities_of_latent_trait_models","285237215_Some_methods_of_strengthening_the_common_ch2_tests","271795097_A_New_Variance_Estimator_for_the_Mantel-Haenszel_Odds_Ratio","268529785_The_Large_Sample_Variance_of_the_Mantel-Haenszel_Estimator_of_a_Common_Odds_Ratio","267654325_Estimators_of_the_Variance_of_the_Mantel-Haenszel_Log-Odds-Ratio_Estimate","266443177_The_detection_of_partial_association_I_The_22_case","265362851_Some_Methods_for_Strengthening_The_Common_X2_Tests","264957527_The_Variance_of_the_Mantel-Haenszel_Estimator","247672787_Detecting_experimentally_induced_item_bias_using_the_iterative_logit_method","240802022_Contingency_Table_Models_for_Assessing_Item_Bias","235361466_Applications_of_Item_Response_Theory_To_Practical_Testing_Problems","230267200_Comparing_distributions_of_item_re